  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Lesions, polyps and other abnormalities in the gastrointestinal (GI) tract have a different
      composition compared to the normal mucose. The investigators plan to gather spectroscopic
      information from these features. Characterizing their unique spectrums, may help to enhance
      the detection and identification of these objects during endoscopy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
